snippet: Michelle Wie, who was partnered with the 15-year-old Lydia Ko at the first women’s major of the year Thursday, has become immune to the sting of criticism.
abstract: Profile of Michelle Wie, who partnered with15-year-old Lydia Ko at Kraft Nabisco Championship, first women’s major of 2013; Wie, whose golf career has stalled, has learned to shrug off her critics.
lead_paragraph: Michelle Wie, who was partnered with the 15-year-old Lydia Ko at the first women’s major of the year Thursday, has become immune to the sting of criticism.

headline.seo: A Veteran at Age 23, Wie Learns to Shake Off Her Critics
headline.main: Wie, Now a Veteran at 23, Learns to Shrug Off Her Critics
